Privacy Policy
Socket Mobile Privacy Policy
We respect your privacy and are committed to your protection
Please review the nature, scope, and purposes of our data collection and how we process your personal data. Socket Mobile reserves the right to update these policies at any time and invites you to visit this policy regularly.
Personal information or Data
is any information related to a person that can be used to identify him/her directly or indirectly. Such information includes name, photo, email address, personal address, device Bluetooth address, bank or credit card details, or online identifiers such as a cookie ID or IP address. For the purposes of GDPR, Personal Information or Data means any information relating to You such as a name, an identification number, location data, online identifier or to one or more factors specific to the physical, physiological, genetic, mental, economic, cultural or social identity.
Our Website
- We’ve structured our website so that you can visit Socket Mobile at www.socketmobile.com and our affiliated web-based Socket Stores without identifying yourself or revealing any personal information (with the exception of optional sections that require registration and/or login.)
When you visit our internet website, we collect the data transmitted to our server by your browser.
During your visit, only data that are technically necessary will be collected.
Processing is carried out in the legitimate interest of improving the site’s stability and features.
The data will not, under any circumstances, be transmitted or used for any other purpose.
We may use cookies to collect website usage data. We place cookies on selected website pages to help us analyze website usage. We do not use cookies to collect personal information.
Certain Definitions
- The following terms used herein mean the following for GDPR-specific purposes.
"Data Controller,"
for the purposes of the GDPR (General Data Protection Regulation), refers to the Company as the legal person which alone or jointly with others determines the purposes and means of the processing of Personal Information or Data.
"Service Provider"
means any natural or legal person who processes the data on behalf of the Company. It refers to third-party companies or individuals employed by the Company to facilitate the Service, to provide the Service on behalf of the Company, to perform services related to the Service or to assist the Company in analyzing how the Service is used. For the purpose of the GDPR, Service Providers are considered Data Processors.
"You"
means the individual accessing or using the Service, the Website the company, or other legal entity on behalf of which such individual is accessing or using the Service, as applicable. Under GDPR (General Data Protection Regulation), You can be referred to as the Data Subject or as the User as you are the individual using the Service.
There are some optional sections within our website that may require you to login and/or register by providing personal information in order to gain access. When we collect your personal information:
We only request the minimum personal information needed to support your relationship with us.
When you provide personal information to us, you consent to the collection of personal information, but you have the right to withdraw your consent or restrict the use or processing of your personal information pursuant to this policy.
We do not sell, rent, or lease your personal information to other organizations or companies.
We do not provide your personal information to others except to selected third-party processors who assist us in fulfilling your requests, such as shipping of product or processing of payment, and who are committed to protecting your personal information.
We will share personal information outside of Socket Mobile if we have a good-faith belief that access, use, preservation, or disclosure of the information is reasonably necessary to:
Meet any applicable law, regulation, legal process, or enforceable governmental request;
Enforce applicable
Terms of Use
, including investigation of potential violations.
Detect, prevent, or otherwise address fraud, security, or technical issues.
Protect against harm to the rights, property, or safety of Socket Mobile, our users, or the public as required or permitted by law; and
To investigate and respond to complaints/disputes.
We may share non-personally identifiable information publicly and with our partners, such as publishers, advertisers, developers, or rights holders. For example, we share information publicly to show trends in the general use of our services. We also allow specific partners to collect information from your browser or device for advertising and measurement purposes using their own cookies or similar technologies.
Legal Basis for Processing Personal Data under GDPR.
We may process Personal Information or Data under the following conditions:
Consent:
You have given Your consent for processing Personal Data for one or more specific purposes.
Performance of a contract:
Provision of Personal Data is necessary for the performance of an agreement with You and/or for any pre-contractual obligations thereof.
Legal obligations:
Processing Personal Data is necessary for compliance with a legal obligation to which the Company is subject.
Vital interests:
Processing Personal Data is necessary in order to protect Your vital interests or of another natural person.
Public interests:
Processing Personal Data is related to a task that is carried out in the public interest or in the exercise of official authority vested in the Company.
Legitimate interests:
Processing Personal Data is necessary for the purposes of the legitimate interests pursued by the Company.
In any case, the Company will gladly help to clarify the specific legal basis that applies to the processing, and in particular whether the provision of Personal Information or Data is a statutory or contractual requirement, or a requirement necessary to enter into a contract.
